column10: Driver rolled through red light making a right turn almost hitting me before I stepped out into the crosswalk.  I had a walk sign.

Driver had to slam on to brakes as he was attempting to make a right-on-red off of Reed Avenue onto northbound Rt. 1. Driver was not paying attention to the crosswalk (which had a walk light) and came about a foot away from hitting me and my dog.
